{"word":"εὐνάζω","slug":"εὐνάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐνάζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εὐνή'><el>εὐνή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to lay</i> or <i>place in ambush</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to put to bed</i>: of animals, <i>to lay</i> their young <i>in a form</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of death, <i>to lay asleep</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to go to bed, sleep</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, attic; of fowls, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—of pain, <el>εὐνασθέντος κακοῦ</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a>, like <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <i>to sleep</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}